With all the forests, volcanoes, animals, fish, and other elements, nature forms a tremendously large system, which exists independently on the planet. However, the notion nature can be interpreted in several different ways; material universe, that which is not artificial or human-made, and part of Earth which is not human-made. The most common meaning, however, is the third one, which encompasses everything on this planet that the human had not altered or made. This multitude of living organisms, plants, and substances stipulates life on Earth in all forms. But humans, as the most intelligent mammals, destroy nature in exchange for science, technology and manufacturing.
